                <li>• Reduces costs of raw material extraction</li>
                <li>• Supports local recycling businesses</li>
                <li>• Provides affordable refurbished electronics</li>
                <li>• Reduces landfill disposal costs</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-green-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-3">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-600">Social Benefits</h4>
              </div>
              <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li>• Provides electronics to underserved communities</li>
                <li>• Reduces digital divide through refurbishment</li>
                <li>• Supports educational programs</li>
                <li>• Improves public health outcomes</li>
                <li>• Enhances community environmental awareness</li>
                <li>• Creates skill development opportunities</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Visual break with data security image -->
        <div class="relative mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <img src="/images/data-security.jpg" alt="Data security and electronics recycling" class="w-full h-64 object-cover">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-l from-blue-900/80 to-transparent flex items-center justify-end">
            <div class="px-8 text-right">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Secure Data Destruction</h3>
              <p class="text-blue-100">Protect your personal information with certified data wiping services.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-8 rounded-lg mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-blue-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">How to Prepare Electronics for Recycling</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">1</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Data Security</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Remove or destroy all personal data before recycling. Use data wiping software or physically remove hard drives. Many recycling centers offer secure data destruction services. For smartphones, perform a factory reset and remove SIM cards. Back up important files to cloud storage first.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">2</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Remove Batteries</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Take out any removable batteries. They often require separate recycling processes. Many electronics stores accept batteries for recycling. Check for swollen or damaged batteries. These need special handling. Store batteries in original packaging or tape terminals.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">3</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Check for Trade-In Value</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Working devices may have trade-in value with manufacturers or retailers. Check manufacturer programs before recycling. Apple, Samsung, and Best Buy offer trade-in programs. Compare trade-in values across multiple platforms for the best return.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">4</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Find Certified Recyclers</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Look for R2 or e-Stewards certified facilities. These certifications ensure responsible handling of electronics. Avoid unlicensed collectors who may export waste abroad. Verify certifications on official websites before dropping off items.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">5</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Prepare for Transport</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Package electronics safely to prevent damage during transport. Use original boxes when available. Separate CRT monitors and TVs due to their weight. Check recycler requirements for specific packaging instructions.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Visual break with broken electronics image -->
        <div class="relative mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <img src="/images/broken-tv.jpeg" alt="Broken electronics ready for recycling" class="w-full h-64 object-cover">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-l from-red-900/80 to-transparent flex items-center justify-end">
            <div class="px-8 text-right">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">End of Life Electronics</h3>
              <p class="text-red-100">When electronics break or become obsolete, proper recycling recovers valuable materials.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-blue-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
